      <prefercite id="aspace_cite">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Osvaldo Böhm Photograph Collection: Art and Architecture of Venice</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_sc">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Photographic survey of buildings in Venice and the Veneto (Chioggia, Padua), mostly ecclesiastical architecture and sculpture, by the firm of Osvaldo Böhm, Fotografo Editore, Veneiza, S. Moise 1349-50. Photographs stamped on the reserve with Böhm inventory numbers, handwritten subject identification in Italian. Some duplicates. A few photographs are not stamped "Böhm" but are from otherwise identifiable sources including Alinari, Gabinetto Fotografico Nazionale (Rome), etc. Total of 506 photographs</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_arr1">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>4 boxes with 16 folders, some folders with additional sub-folders labeled by building.</p>  
      </arrangement>
